Description: Small fragment of a seal-impression, the fine brown Nile clay has some mica inclusions and was hardened after excavation. The rear shows several turned string impressions. At the side finger impressions and what might be impressions of textile. The top bears part of a seal-impression with a circumferential line. On the left a small cartouche with wsr-mAa.t and maybe a corner of mrj underneath, rest broken off. Above the cartouche a small sun-disc. To the right of the cartouche further signs, illegible.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), E14.7 temple magazine
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
